The numbers are written on a hexagonal grid spiral. We first determine the layer $k$ that the number $N=2026$ belongs to.

The maximum number in layer $k$ is $M_k = 1 + 3k(k+1)$.
For $k=25$, $M_{25} = 1 + 3(25)(26) = 1951$.
For $k=26$, $M_{26} = 1 + 3(26)(27) = 2107$.
Since $1951 < 2026 \le 2107$, the number 2026 is in Layer $k=26$. The length of each segment $L$ in this layer is $k=26$.

The layer starts at $N_{start} = 1952$. The total number of positions covered in Layer 26 is $2026 - 1951 = 75$.
The segments $S_i$ have length $L=26$.
$75 = 2 \times 26 + 23$. This means 2026 is in the 3rd segment ($S_3$).

$S_1$ runs $1952$ to $1977$.
$S_2$ runs $1978$ to $2003$.
$S_3$ runs $2004$ to $2029$.
$N=2026$ is $p=22$ steps along $S_3$ (since $2026 = 2004 + 22$).

A cell $X$ on Layer $k$ that is not a corner has 6 neighbors: 2 on the same layer (along the path), 2 on Layer $k-1$ (inward), and 2 on Layer $k+1$ (outward).

