For the hexagonal spiral, the neighbors of $X$ that lie in $L_{k-1}$ are known to be $C_{k-1, i-1} + (k-j)$ and $C_{k-1, i} - j$.
Here $i=3$, $j=3$ (steps remaining until $C_{26, 3}$).
$C_{25, 2} = 1851$. $C_{25, 3} = 1876$. $k=26$.
$Y_A = 1851 + (26 - 3) = 1874$.
$Y_B = 1876 - 3 = 1873$.

